p%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20nice%20and%20durable.%20The%20plastic%20housing%20has%20heavy-duty%20molded%20rubber%20protecting%20most%20of%20the%20edges%20and%20corners%20that%20could%20otherwise%20get%20dinged%20up%20from%20drops%20and%20falls.%20Whether%20you're%20a%20DIY-er%20who%20doesn't%20need%20a%20bulkier%20option%20or%20you%20just%20want%20a%20capable%20drill%20to%20supplement%20your%2020V%20powerhouse%2C%20this%20drill%20makes%20a%20great%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hand%20holding%20red%20Milwaukee%20M18%20Fuel%20Surge%2018-Volt%20cordless%20drill%20while%20inserting%20screw%20into%20cabinet%2C%20one%20of%20the%20best%20cordless%20drills%20of%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F626838a22bd7770018cf0291%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Milwaukee%202760-20%20M18%20Fuel%20Surge%2018-Volt%20Hex%20Impact%20Driver%20is%20an%20excellent%20pick%20for%20jobs%20where%20you%20need%20to%20sink%20screws%20only.%3Cp%3EThe%20Home%20Depot%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226b3b0d06-1f14-489b-b0b3-dd62402b3ec5%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Best%20impact%20driver%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBest%20impact%20driver%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMilwaukee%202760-20%20M18%20Fuel%20Surge%2018-Volt%20Hex%20Impact%20Driver%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESmall%20size%2C%20includes%20%26quot%3Bself-tapping%20screw%20mode%2C%26quot%3B%20can%20produce%203000%20RPMs%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Only%20designed%20for%20screwing%20fasteners%2C%20battery%20not%20included%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20take%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhat%20it%20lacks%20in%20versatility%2C%20the%20Milwaukee%20M18%20Fuel%20Surge%2018-Volt%20impact%20driver%20makes%20up%20for%20in%20performance.%20It's%20specifically%20designed%20to%20sink%20a%20ton%20of%20fasteners%20with%20minimum%20user%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%3Ccolgroup%3E%3Ccol%3E%3Ccol%3E%3C%2Fcolgroup%3E%3Ctbody%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%3EMilwaukee%202760-20%20M18%20Fuel%20Surge%2018-Volt%20Hex%20Impact%20Driver%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3ESpecs%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20included%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EDriver%20only%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EModel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E2760-20%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeight%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E2.1%20lbs%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EVoltage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E18V%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftbody%3E%3C%2Ftable%3E%3Cp%3EImpact%20drivers%20like%20the%20Milwaukee%20M18%20Fuel%20Surge%2018-Volt%20differ%20from%20typical%20drills%20in%20that%20they%20only%20perform%20one%20job%3A%20driving%20fasteners.%20This%20does%20limit%20their%20range%20%E2%80%94%20but%20if%20you%20need%20to%20sink%20a%20lot%20of%20screws%20with%20little%20effort%2C%20an%20impact%20driver%20is%20superior%20to%20almost%20anything.%20Impact%20drivers%20use%20a%20concussive%20force%20to%20drive%20fasteners%2C%20but%20unlike%20hammer-drills%20that%20create%20downward%20force%20(think%20hitting%20the%20back%20of%20the%20drill%20with%20a%20hammer)%2C%20impact%20drivers%20work%20by%20applying%20that%20force%20to%20the%20spinning%20motion%20of%20the%20bit.%20This%20increases%20the%20amount%20of%20torque%20they%20can%20create%2C%20which%20is%20why%20they%20work%20so%20effectively.%20Impact%20drivers%20are%20also%20more%20compact%20than%20other%20drills%2C%20and%20the%20Fuel%20Surge%20model%20is%20no%20different.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20other%20impact%20drivers%20that%20use%20a%20hammer%20mechanism%20to%20generate%20their%20torque%2C%20the%20Surge%20design%20uses%20a%20hydraulic%20pump.%20That%20means%20this%20impact%20driver%20produces%20less%20torque%20overall%2C%20but%20it%20maintains%20this%20torque%20for%20a%20longer%20length%20of%20time.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20you%20get%20a%20smoother%20operation%2C%20less%20vibration%20and%20noise%2C%20and%20a%20more%20comfortable%20tool.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20particular%20option%20is%20%26quot%3Btool-only%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20means%20it%20doesn't%20come%20with%20a%20battery.%20These%20options%20are%20substantially%20cheaper%20but%20only%20make%20sense%20if%20you%20already%20own%20a%20few%2018V%20Milwaukee%20tools%20and%20have%20a%20supply%20of%20batteries%20already.%20If%20this%20is%20your%20first%2018V%20Milwaukee%20tool%2C%20you'll%20need%20to%20buy%20a%20separate%20battery%20and%20charger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222a054a2b-11a6-44f2-a280-8ec2ec43b4b5%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20to%20look%20for%20in%20cordless%20drills%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20cordless%20drills%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20shopping%20for%20the%20best%20cordless%20drill%20for%20your%20needs%2C%20it%20can%20help%20to%20consider%20these%20factors%3A%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVoltage%20and%20amp%20hours%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECordless%20drills%20measure%20power%20in%20battery%20voltage%2C%20which%20can%20range%20from%206V%20all%20the%20way%20up%20to%2024V.%20%26quot%3BHigher%20voltage%20means%20more%20torque-spinning%20strength%20to%20overcome%20resistance%2C%26quot%3B%20Horton%20says.%20Amp%20hours%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20measure%20the%20runtime%20of%20the%20battery.%20The%20amp%20hour%20rating%20can%20best%20be%20described%20as%20the%20'fuel%20tank'%20of%20the%20battery%2C%20Horton%20says.%20The%20higher%20the%20value%2C%20the%20larger%20the%20tank%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20longer%20you%20can%20run%20your%20cordless%20power%20tool%20on%20a%20single%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicholas%20says%20a%20larger%20voltage%20drill%20will%20produce%20more%20force%20%E2%80%94%20great%20if%20you're%20trying%20to%20drill%20a%20big%20hole%20through%20a%20brick%20wall%20%E2%80%94%20but%20will%20draw%20more%20amps%2C%20thus%20draining%20the%20battery%20quicker.%20An%2018V%20drill%20will%20drain%20a%202%20amp%20hour%20battery%20quicker%20than%20a%2010.8V%20drill%20will%20drain%20the%20same%20battery%20size.%20According%20to%20Nicholas%2C%20you%20can%20think%20of%20voltage%20as%20the%20size%20of%20a%20water%20pump.%20The%20greater%20the%20voltage%2C%20the%20bigger%20the%20pump.%20%26quot%3BAmp%20hours%20are%20the%20size%20of%20the%20water%20tank.%20The%20bigger%20the%20tank%2C%20the%20longer%20the%20supply%20lasts.%20The%20size%20of%20the%20pump%20and%20how%20hard%20you%20run%20it%20affects%20how%20quickly%20the%20water%20empties%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicholas%20says.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETorque%20and%20speed%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETorque%20is%20the%20amount%20of%20rotational%20force%20the%20drill%20can%20generate.%20Heavy-duty%20jobs%20like%20drilling%20into%20solid%20wood%20require%20a%20lot%20of%20torque%2C%20while%20lighter-duty%20tasks%20like%20drilling%20through%20plasterboard%20need%20less%20torque.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20be%20careful%20of%20excessive%20torque%20as%20this%20makes%20the%20drill%20difficult%20to%20control%2C%20causing%20it%20to%20bounce%20around%20and%20damage%20the%20screws%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicholas%20says.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20speed%20of%20a%20drill%20describes%20how%20fast%20it%20can%20rotate.%20But%20according%20to%20Nicholas%2C%20higher%20speed%20doesn't%20necessarily%20equal%20better%20performance.%20%26quot%3BDifferent%20materials%20have%20different%20speeds%20at%20which%20they%20should%20be%20drilled%20through%2C%20so%20it's%20always%20worth%20clarifying%20before%20you%20start%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicholas%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20you%20can%20often%20get%20this%20info%20with%20a%20quick%20Google%20search.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you%20try%20to%20drill%20through%20aluminum%20at%20high%20speed%2C%20the%20drill%20bit%20will%20overheat%20and%20go%20blunt.%20So%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20maintain%20a%20slow%20speed%20that%20keeps%20the%20drill%20bit%20cool.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHorton%20says%20it's%20important%20to%20understand%20the%20inverse%20relationship%20between%20torque%20and%20speed.%20%26quot%3BAs%20you%20increase%20speed%2C%20you%20actually%20decrease%20torque%20%E2%80%94%20but%20when%20you%20drill%20at%20a%20low%20speed%2C%20you%20can%20access%20the%20most%20torque%20a%20drill%20has%20to%20offer%2C%26quot%3B%20Horton%20says.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESize%2C%20weight%2C%20and%20chuck%20size%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDepending%20on%20your%20needs%20and%20projects%2C%20bigger%20isn't%20always%20better%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20cordless%20drills.%20If%20you%20don't%20need%20the%20power%20of%20a%20large%20drill%2C%20you%20might%20end%20up%20with%20a%20bulky%2C%20heavy%20tool%20that's%20inconvenient%20and%20uncomfortable%20to%20use.%20Smaller%2C%20less%20powerful%20drills%20have%20a%20lighter%20weight%20that's%20often%20easier%20to%20control.%20They%20also%20prove%20useful%20for%20jobs%20with%20awkward%20working%20areas%2C%20like%20reaching%20into%20the%20back%20of%20a%20cabinet%20or%20installing%20overhead%20hinges.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECordless%20drills%20have%20an%20adjustable%20chuck%2C%20which%20is%20the%20tip%20of%20the%20drill%20that%20holds%20the%20bit%20in%20place.%20The%20chuck%20size%20refers%20to%20the%20maximum%20diameter%20of%20bits%20it%20can%20accept.%20Smaller%20drills%20usually%20have%20%C2%BC-inch%20chucks%2C%20medium-sized%20drills%20have%20%E2%85%9C-inch%20chucks%2C%20and%20the%20largest%20drills%20have%20%C2%BD-inch%20chucks.%20The%20best%20cordless%20drills%20generally%20have%20an%20adjustable%20chuck%2C%20which%20allows%20you%20to%20use%20the%20same%20tool%20for%20a%20range%20of%20tasks%2C%20from%20heavy-duty%20construction%20projects%20to%20quick%20household%20maintenance%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBrushed%20vs%20brushless%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhen%20shopping%20for%20drills%2C%20you%20might%20notice%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bbrushless%20motor%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20refers%20to%20the%20design%20of%20the%20motor%20and%20the%20mechanism%20it%20uses%20to%20spin%20the%20chuck.%20All%20cordless%20drills%20use%20magnets%20to%20spin%20the%20chuck%20of%20the%20drill.%20In%20brushed%20motors%2C%20small%20metal%20brushes%20propel%20these%20magnets.%20Brushless%20motors%20eliminate%20the%20need%20for%20these%20brushes.%20This%20makes%20the%20drill%20smaller%20and%20lighter%20while%20also%20reducing%20friction%2C%20increasing%20efficiency%2C%20and%20extending%20battery%20runtime.%20%26quot%3BWithout%20brushes%20to%20cause%20friction%20and%20slow%20things%20down%2C%20brushless%20drills%20pack%20more%20power%20and%20torque%20and%20can%20reach%20higher%20speeds%2C%26quot%3B%20Horton%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20you%20can%20expect%20a%2015%25%20to%2035%25%20increase%20in%20performance%20compared%20with%20a%20brushed%20motor%20drill.%20With%20the%20exception%20of%20our%20budget%20pick%2C%20our%20picks%20for%20the%20best%20cordless%20drill%20all%20include%20brushless%20motors.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERuntime%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAll%20cordless%20drills%20have%20a%20limited%20runtime%2C%20but%20the%20lithium-ion%20batteries%20used%20today%20can%20last%20much%20longer%20than%20older%20NiCD%20or%20NiMH%20types.%20A%20larger%20battery%20will%20typically%20provide%20higher%20amp%20hours%2C%20which%20can%20help%20extend%20your%20drill's%20runtime%20and%20reduce%20time%20spent%20recharging%20during%20a%20project.%20If%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20heavier%2C%20bulkier%20battery%2C%20you%20can%20also%20choose%20a%20drill%20that%20comes%20with%20multiple%20smaller%20batteries.%20This%20allows%20you%20to%20have%20a%20battery%20charging%20at%20all%20times%20so%20you%20can%20quickly%20swap%20them%20out%20as%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBatteries%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhile%20models%20that%20come%20with%20more%20than%20one%20battery%20may%20have%20a%20higher%20price%20tag%2C%20they%20typically%20cost%20less%20upfront%20than%20you'll%20pay%20if%20you%20need%20to%20buy%20an%20additional%20battery%20later%20on.%20Remember%2C%20too%2C%20that%20a%20battery%20with%20a%20higher%20amp%20hours%20(AH)%20rating%20will%20have%20more%20power%20and%20run%20longer.%20%26quot%3BA%204.0%20AH%20battery%20will%20run%20twice%20as%20long%20as%20a%202.0%20AH%20battery%2C%26quot%3B%20Horton%20says.%20That%20said%2C%20batteries%20with%20higher%20AH%20are%20physically%20bigger%20and%20heavier.%20This%20could%20be%20a%20downside%20if%20you%20need%20to%20hook%20your%20drill%20on%20your%20tool%20belt%20for%20the%20day%20or%20use%20it%20in%20tight%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22743a1897-552c-414d-ae38-31ca554635dd%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20we%20selected%20cordless%20drills%5C%22%3EHow%20we%20selected%20cordless%20drills%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20narrow%20down%20the%20best%20cordless%20drill%2C%20I%20used%20my%20personal%20experience%20as%20a%20residential%20carpenter%20and%20consulted%20two%20experts.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBobby%20Horton%20owns%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftriangleremodeling.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETriangle%20Remodeling%20Service%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20shared%20his%20vast%20expertise%20to%20help%20us%20understand%20the%20%26quot%3Bcordless%26quot%3B%20component%20of%20cordless%20drills%2C%20specifically%20how%20their%20batteries%20affect%20performance.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDave%20Nicholas%20is%20a%20professional%20electrician%20and%20founder%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsparkybase.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESparkyBase.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20helped%20explain%20the%20functionality%20and%20operational%20capabilities%20of%20cordless%20drills%20with%20helpful%20real-world%20examples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22952fd609-3b87-4f3e-8bcb-2baaa9d4ab3d%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Cordless%20drill%20FAQs%5C%22%3ECordless%20drill%20FAQs%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat's%20a%20clutch%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20cordless%20drill%20will%20have%20two%20basic%20settings%3A%20the%20clutch%20and%20speed%20settings.%20The%20clutch%20is%20the%20numbered%20collar%20on%20the%20front%20of%20the%20drill%20that%20allows%20you%20to%20adjust%20how%20much%20torque%20your%20drill%20produces.%20Torque%20refers%20to%20the%20amount%20of%20rotational%20force%20your%20drill%20applies%20to%20the%20fastener%20you're%20working%20with.%20This%20setting%20is%20important%20because%20different%20tasks%20require%20different%20amounts%20of%20torque.%20Too%20much%20torque%20can%20damage%20the%20material%20you're%20working%20with.%20Not%20enough%20torque%20means%20your%20drill%20won't%20have%20the%20power%20it%20needs%20to%20spin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20clutch%20setting%20should%20I%20use%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EApplying%20the%20correct%20amount%20of%20torque%20can%20be%20tricky%20at%20first%2C%20but%20you%20can%20start%20with%20this%20rule%20of%20thumb%3A%20the%20larger%20the%20fastener%2C%20the%20higher%20amount%20of%20torque%20you%20want.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you're%20using%20tiny%20screws%20to%20build%20a%20birdhouse%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20keep%20the%20clutch%20dialed%20down%20pretty%20low.%20If%20you're%20cranking%20out%20a%20big%20lug%20nut%20on%20a%20piece%20of%20machinery%2C%20you'll%20want%20much%20more%20torque.%20When%20you%20aren't%20sure%20how%20much%20torque%20you%20need%2C%20aim%20to%20start%20low%20and%20work%20your%20way%20up.%20If%20you%20don't%20use%20enough%20torque%20and%20the%20fastener%20gives%20you%20much%20resistance%2C%20the%20clutch%20will%20disengage%20the%20motor.%20This%20is%20a%20good%20thing%2C%20as%20it%20prevents%20you%20from%20stripping%20the%20fastener%20or%20breaking%20your%20drill%20bit.%20From%20there%2C%20you%20can%20ratchet%20up%20the%20torque%20another%20notch%20and%20try%20again%20%E2%80%94%20repeating%20until%20you%20find%20the%20sweet%20spot%20that%20provides%20enough%20torque%20to%20do%20the%20job%20but%20not%20so%20much%20that%20it%20damages%20the%20fastener%20or%20the%20wood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20speed%20setting%20should%20I%20use%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20cordless%20drills%20have%20two%20or%20three%20speeds%20to%20choose%20from.%20These%20speed%20settings%20combine%20with%20the%20torque%20settings%20to%20allow%20you%20to%20dial%20in%20the%20drill%20with%20precision.%20Lower%20speeds%20and%20higher%20torque%20settings%20work%20best%20for%20driving%20big%20fasteners%2C%20while%20high%20speed%20and%20%2Flow%20torque%20combinations%20work%20well%20for%20smaller%20fasteners%20and%20drilling%20small%20holes.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20batteries%20are%20used%20in%20cordless%20drills%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20new%20cordless%20drill%20you%20purchase%20will%20have%20a%20lithium%20ion%20battery.%20These%20batteries%20have%20replaced%20two%20older%20battery%20types%3A%20nickel-cadmium%20and%20nickel-metal%20hydride.%20Lithium%20ion%20batteries%20have%20a%20smaller%20size%20and%20require%20less%20maintenance%20than%20these%20older%20types%2C%20Horton%20says%2C%20and%20they're%20pretty%20much%20standard%20in%20cordless%20drills%20these%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20size%20drill%20do%20I%20need%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20average%20homeowner%20would%20do%20fine%20with%20either%20an%2018v%20or%2020v%20cordless%20drill%2C%26quot%3B%20Horton%20says.%20Nicholas%20adds%20that%20an%2018V%20drill%20can%20handle%20most%20situations%20a%20home%20renovator%20can%20throw%20at%20it.%20%26quot%3BAn%2018V%20drill%20has%20a%20comfortable%20size%2C%20and%20the%20torque%20s