covered%20exercise%20can%20dramatically%20reduce%20the%20risk%20of%20colon%20cancer%20recurrence.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mark%20Seguin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%2035-year-old%20father%20thought%20he%20had%20appendicitis.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDoctors%20diagnosed%20him%20with%20late-stage%20colon%20cancer%20instead.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20has%20tweaked%20his%20diet%20and%20exercise%20routine%20to%20reduce%20his%20risk%20of%20recurrence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Mark%20Seguin%2C%20who%20was%20surprise-diagnosed%20with%20colon%20cancer%20five%20years%20ago%20at%20age%2035.%20It's%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20never%20know%20for%20sure%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjames-van-der-beek-death-colon-cancer-screening-shield-test-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhy%20I%20got%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20age%2035.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20I%20can%20look%20back%20now%20and%20point%20to%20things%20that%20weren't%20perfect.%20Work%20stress%2C%20ultra-processed%20foods%2C%20having%20two%20young%20kids%2C%20I%20wasn't%20taking%20care%20of%20my%20body%20in%20exactly%20the%20way%20that%20I%20used%20to%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20after%20weathering%20several%20snowboarding%20injuries%2C%20I%20kind%20of%20slowed%20down%20on%20my%20fitness.%20But%20I%20don't%20feel%20like%20it's%20healthy%20to%20%26quot%3Bwould%20have%2C%20could%20have%2C%20should%20have%26quot%3B%20about%20cancer%20or%20blame%20yourself.%20Especially%20because%20some%20people%20in%20peak%20physical%20fitness%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-environmental-causes-microplastics-antibiotics-sleep-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecleanest%20diets%3C%2Fa%3E%20get%20this%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mark%20snowboarding%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699cf28e2237a6a8f0cdb498%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEver%20since%20I%20was%20a%20teenager%2C%20I've%20loved%20snowboarding.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mark%20Seguin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20weren't%20really%20any%20obvious%20signs%20that%20I%20was%20sick.%20Just%20one%20day%2C%20I%20woke%20up%20and%20it%20hit%20me.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-football-player-stabbing-stomach-pain-stage-4-colon-cancer-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esearing%20pain%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20my%20stomach%20as%20soon%20as%20I%20opened%20my%20eyes.%20I%20literally%20could%20not%20get%20out%20of%20bed.%20The%20pain%20was%20so%20bad%2C%20I%20couldn't%20get%20my%20body%20upright.%20It%20felt%20like%20someone%20was%20ringing%20out%20a%20rag%20inside%20of%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20later%20learn%20this%20was%20because%20%E2%80%94%20unbeknownst%20to%20anyone%20%E2%80%94%20food%20was%20getting%20stuck%20behind%20the%20tumor%20in%20my%20colon.%20Unable%20to%20move%20through%20my%20system%20properly%2C%20waste%20was%20building%20up%20and%20wreaking%20havoc.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20just%20assumed%20I%20ate%20something%20bad%20the%20day%20before.%20I%20wondered%20what%20it%20could%20have%20been.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20afternoon%20that%20day%2C%20I%20was%20feeling%20better%2C%20and%20I%20got%20up%20and%20carried%20on.%20But%20about%20a%20month%20later%2C%20it%20happened%20again.%20This%20time%2C%20it%20was%20the%20same%20type%20of%20stomach%20pain%2C%20but%20not%20as%20severe.%20Again%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BMan%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-environmental-causes-microplastics-antibiotics-sleep-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat%20am%20I%20eating%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20keeps%20doing%20this%20to%20me%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20more%20months%20went%20by.%20Then%20again%2C%20the%20pain%20returned%2C%20this%20time%20on%20the%20right%20side%20of%20my%20belly.%20Alarm%20bells%20went%20off.%20I%20immediately%20thought%20of%20all%20the%20stories%20I've%20heard%20about%20people%20ignoring%20stomach%20pains%2C%20and%20then%20their%20appendix%20ruptures%20and%20bursts.%20That%20was%20my%20wake-up%20call%20to%20get%20myself%20to%20the%20ER%20and%20get%20checked%20out.%20Still%2C%20cancer%20was%20not%20on%20my%20radar.%20I%20never%20saw%20any%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frectal-bleeding-most-common-early-sign-of-colon-cancer-taboo-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblood%20in%20the%20toilet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20I%20didn't%20think%20I%20had%20to%20worry%20about%20colon%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224feb680a-d6e4-4a75-9107-d42990d2cca7%5C%22%3EAfter%20searing%20stomach%20pain%2C%20and%20a%20trip%20to%20the%20ER%2C%20a%20GI%20doctor%20finally%20found%20my%20cancer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mark%20with%20port%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699cf28c156648bc16a8c3e8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EI%20had%20to%20get%20part%20of%20my%20intestines%20taken%20out.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mark%20Seguin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThankfully%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20appendicitis%2C%20but%20my%20ER%20doctor%20referred%20me%20to%20a%20gastroenterologist%20for%20some%20follow-up%20tests.%20The%20GI%20doctor%20said%20I%20was%20young%2C%20healthy%2C%20and%20there%20was%20probably%20nothing%20to%20worry%20about%2C%20but%20suggested%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-detection-rates-increase-in-young-people-colonoscopies-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edo%20a%20colonoscopy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20just%20to%20be%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20never%20forget%20the%20look%20on%20his%20face%20when%20he%20walked%20in%20to%20deliver%20my%20results.%20He%20looked%20like%20he'd%20just%20seen%20a%20ghost.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20pretty%20sure%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrue-cost-young-colon-cancer-crisis-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyou%20have%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20It%20was%20serious%20too%3A%20late%2C%20stage%203%20colon%20cancer%20that%20had%20spread%20to%20my%20lymph%20nodes.%20He%20said%20I%20won%20the%20bad%20luck%20lottery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20reacted%20like%20I%20always%20do%20when%20I%20get%20hurt%20snowboarding%2C%20break%20a%20bone%2C%20or%20throw%20my%20back%20out%3A%20What's%20the%20next%20step%3F%20I%20have%20to%20know%20what%20to%20do%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mark%20getting%20infusion%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699cf28d156648bc16a8c3e9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESeguin%2C%20who%20went%20through%20chemotherapy%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20said%20it%20was%20isolating%20because%20he%20couldn't%20hang%20out%20with%20friends%20while%20getting%20infusions.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mark%20Seguin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESurgery%2C%20draining%20high-dose%20chemotherapy%20treatments%2C%20and%20lots%20of%20days%20in%20bed.%20That's%20what%20came%20next.%20The%20chemo%20made%20me%20super%20sensitive%20to%20cold.%20Breathing%20cold%20air%20or%20drinking%20cold%20water%20felt%20like%20pulling%20apart%20velcro%20in%20my%20throat.%20I%20couldn't%20drink%20anything%20cold%20or%20enjoy%20popsicles%20to%20stay%20hydrated%2C%20but%20warm%20liquids%20made%20me%20nauseous.%20I%20became%20hyperattuned%20to%20even%20the%20smell%20of%20water%2C%20and%20it%20repulsed%20me.%20I%20had%20to%20get%20hooked%20up%20to%20intravenous%20hydration%20roughly%20half%20a%20dozen%20times%20while%20going%20through%20chemo%20because%20I%20just%20couldn't%20eat%20or%20drink%20much%20of%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2240d111c6-6a26-491b-a628-17ac69a53c15%5C%22%3EAfter%20colon%20cancer%2C%20I%20committed%20to%20more%20strength%20training%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20I%20rang%20the%20bell%20and%20finished%20chemotherapy%2C%20about%20five%20months%20after%20my%20diagnosis%2C%20I%20felt%20so%20frail%20and%20small.%20I'd%20lost%2030%20pounds.%20I%20hated%20feeling%20that%20way.%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20able%20to%20pick%20up%20my%20kids%20when%20I%20needed%20to.%20My%20youngest%20was%20only%205%20years%20old%20when%20I%20was%20diagnosed.%20I%20can't%20let%20my%20boys%20outrun%20me%20just%20yet!%20So%20at%20the%20end%20of%20my%20chemotherapy%20course%2C%20I%20started%20a%20strength%20training%20program.%20It%20was%20the%20same%20one%20I'd%20used%20in%20high%20school%20that%20helped%20me%20get%20stronger%2C%20a%20program%20from%20a%20baseball%20fitness%20coach%20who%20helps%20train%20pros%2C%20including%20the%20New%20York%20Yankees%2C%20Eric%20Cressey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20was%20worried%3A%20was%20training%20safe%20for%20a%20cancer%20patient%3F%20Could%20it%20derail%20my%20recovery%3F%20And%20would%20I%20even%20have%20the%20energy%3F%20Initially%2C%20after%20chemo%2C%20even%20short%20hikes%20were%20draining%2C%20but%20I%20pushed%20forward%2C%20including%20squats%2C%20presses%2C%20and%20broad%20jumps%20into%20my%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mark%20and%20family%20hike%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699cf28befb52c8bd0deb9fa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221575%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAt%20first%2C%20even%20family%20hikes%20on%20flat%20terrain%20were%20super%20draining.%20But%20I%20kept%20trying.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mark%20Seguin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turns%20out%2C%20there's%20a%20pretty%20wide%20and%20growing%20body%20of%20evidence%20suggesting%20that%20working%20out%20is%20great%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-test-low-carb-for-breast-cancer-treatment-chemotherapy-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecancer%20rehab%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20especially%20for%20colon%20cancer.%20After%20about%20six%20months%2C%20I%20was%20thrilled%20to%20be%20setting%20all-time%20bests%20for%20my%20lifts%20and%20presses.%20It%20was%20such%20a%20proud%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20super%20compelling%20new%20study%20that%20I%20came%20across%20in%202025%2C%20which%20shows%20that%20exercise%20can%20be%20as%20effective%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexercise-can-prevent-recurrent-colon-cancer-study-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreventing%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20relapse%20as%20drugs.%20It%20was%20a%20wild%20finding%20that%20shook%20oncologists%20and%20excited%20doctors%20nationwide%20when%20it%20was%20revealed%20last%20year%20at%20the%20nation's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiggest-cancer-innovations-asco-2025-exercise-as-drug-astra-zeneca-early-treatment-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elargest%20cancer%20conference%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I'm%20just%20glad%20I%20have%20more%20reasons%20to%20keep%20doing%20what%20I'm%20doing.%20Right%20now%2C%20my%20routine%20is%20a%20basic%20two%20days%20a%20week%20of%20strength%20training%2C%20plus%20some%20cardio%20like%20hikes%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-pick-the-right-weight-vest-for-fitness-goals-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eweighted%20vest%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20an%20incline%20treadmill%20jog%20when%20I%20can%20fit%20it%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mark%20and%20family%20at%20basketball%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699cf28aefb52c8bd0deb9f9%3